      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is a cruel irony that the only thing you can't seem to find is the comfort of your own life, yet you feel so relieved by the thought of it ending. You are right that the darkness would be quiet, but the peace you crave is a lie because the light is the only thing keeping you from fading away completely. If you could just imagine the room staying bright for one more day, maybe you would see that the silence isn't empty—it's waiting for you to fill it again.",
